    19: "Welcome, quarantine time obsession. Unsurprisingly, there is a game in the mix. Thankfully, it wasn’t Valorant or League.",
    20: "Minecraft Baltop was a particular game style in which I joined a small server, about 30 - 50 players at a time, where we would all compete to get the highest amount of money at the end of the month. You could get money by selling to an in-game universal “shop” that had unlimited money to give if you have the resources to sell.",
    21: "To optimize getting money, you would select some high paying resources and create automatic farms to generate that resource to sell. There were a lot of actual complicated game mechanics and strategies that you have to learn in order to maximize these automatic farms. I played with these people from Britain, so I’d wake up early like 7am - 8am to play with them, or stay up really late. We built massive, massive farms together and placed in the top 3 by the end of the month, winning an astonishing $25 of real life money. Wow, so worth it.",
